DOCUMENT();

loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

#  Setup

Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->are(t => "Real");
Context()->flags->set(useBaseTenLog => 1);
Context()->flags->set(tolerance     => 0.01, tolType => "absolute");

$Q    = 30;
$root = random(10, 15, 1);
$b    = 2**(-1 / $root);
$a    = random(85, 100, 1);
$ans  = Compute("(log($Q)-log($a))/log($b)");

BEGIN_PGML
A travel mug of [`[$a]^{\circ}`]C coffee is left on the roof of a parked car on a cold winter day. The temperature of the coffee after [`t`] minutes is given by 
[``` H = [$a](2)^{-t/[$root]}. ```]

After how many minutes will the coffee be only lukewarm ([`30^{\circ}`]C)? [`t = `] [_]{$ans}
 
END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
In this case, we need to solve the equation:
[```30 = [$a] (2)^{-t/[$root]}```]
divide through by [`[$a]`] 
[```\frac{30}{[$a]} = 2^{-t/[$root]}```]
write this in log form:
[``` -\frac{t}{[$root]} = \frac{\log(30/[$a])}{\log(2)}```]
multiply through by [`-[$root]`]
[```  t = - [$root] \frac{\log(30/[$a])}{\log(2)} = [$ans]```]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

COMMENT('Uses log = log10.');

ENDDOCUMENT();
